senses.sense_definition: A place where two rivers or streams flow together.

examples.text: We hiked down to the <w>watersmeet</w> to see the currents merge.
The village was founded near the <w>watersmeet</w> of the two great rivers.

senses.sense_definition: A township in Michigan, United States.

examples.text: They planned a fishing trip to <w>Watersmeet</w> next summer.
The road to <w>Watersmeet</w> is surrounded by dense forests.

senses.sense_definition: A village in KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa.

examples.text: She was born in a small house in <w>Watersmeet</w>.
Travelers often pass through <w>Watersmeet</w> on their way inland.
